\f0\b \cf0 Installation\

\f1\b0 The Xcode project will build and automatically install this color picker into the user's ColorPickers directory found at -\
\
	
\f2\fs18 ~/Library/ColorPickers/MyColorPicker.colorpicker\

\f1\fs24 \
This is set in the "Installation Directory" option in the Target Build Settings in Xcode.\
\

\f0\b Testing
\f1\b0 \
To test MyColorPicker, you obviously need to launch an application that uses the Color Picker, most conveniently through the Font panel.  TextEdit is a good application for testing purposes.\
\

